Apex Controller
public with sharing class VideoStreamVF {
    public Blob getVideoBlob() {
        StaticResource sr = [
            SELECT Body, ContentType
            FROM StaticResource
            WHERE Name = 'MyVideoResource'
            LIMIT 1
        ];
        ApexPages.currentPage().getHeaders().put('Content-Type', sr.ContentType);
        return sr.Body;
    }
}

Visualforce Page
<apex:page controller="VideoStreamVF" cache="true" contentType="video/mp4">
    {!videoBlob}
</apex:page>


Name the page:

VideoStream


Now test:

https://YOURCOMMUNITYDOMAIN/apex/VideoStream


✔ Should download or stream
✔ NO rest restrictions
✔ Always works for guest users

✅ STEP 4 — Update LWC to use VF URL
videoUrl = '/apex/VideoStream';

LWC HTML:
<video width="600" controls>
    <source src={videoUrl} type="video/mp4" />
</video>
